	<section xml:id="ref.expressions.stop">
		<title><code>stop</code></title>
		<section xml:id="ref.expressions.stop.body">
			<para>
			The <code>stop</code> expression does nothing. Execution of <code>stop</code>
			immediately halts without publishing. 
			</para>
			
			<para>
			<code>stop</code> is often used in conjunction with the <link linkend="ref.combinators.sequential">sequential combinator</link> to make an expression <link linkend="ref.concepts.silence">silent</link>. 
			For example, the expression <replaceable>F</replaceable><code> >> stop</code> behaves as <replaceable>F</replaceable>, except that it is silent, since all of its publications are consumed by <code>stop</code>, which does nothing.
			</para>
		</section>
		
